cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of mobile crowd sensing technologies and IoT, which are related to networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed platform is a distributed sensing platform that utilizes cloud integration, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the processing and management of large volumes of data, which is related to data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper discusses the storage and retrieval of sensor data, which is related to databases. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The proposed platform involves the development of software for mobile sensing and cloud integration, which falls under the scope of software engineering.
